Tiered downsampling for single-node VictoriaMetrics OSS. ~210 line
build-time patch, not a fork. No cluster support.

  -downsampling.period=30d:5m,180d:1h

Last sample per 5m for data older than 30d, per 1h older than 180d.
Same semantics as -dedup.minScrapeInterval, no aggregation. Older tiers
need bigger intervals, divisible by newer ones. Queries thin
immediately, disk reclaimed by the hourly historical merge watcher.

Build:

  ./build.sh v1.148.0
  -> dist/victoria-metrics-linux-amd64-v1.148.0-downsampling.tar.gz

Or: git apply vm-downsampling.patch (older tags: patch -p1 --fuzz=3).
Prebuilt linux-amd64 binaries under releases.

Set retention to cover the data, e.g.
-retentionPeriod=2y -downsampling.period=30d:5m,180d:1h

Apache 2.0, same as upstream. Independent reimplementation, no
enterprise code. Unofficial, not affiliated with VictoriaMetrics, Inc.
